%YAML 1.1
%TAG !u! tag:unity3d.com,2011:
--- !u!114 &11400000
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 53e72f983de76b64da2c3ba9d6e008e2, type: 3}
  m_Name: GuideBookData
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::GuideBookData
  pages:
  - title: Movement
    bodyText: 'Every step counts. Each turn, you can navigate to any adjacent hex
      highlighted in Yellow. These highlights represent your valid paths across the
      battlefield.

      You begin your journey with 1 Move per turn. Choose your
      path wisely, but keep an eye out for powerful Perks that grant extra moves,
      allowing you to outmaneuver even the swiftest foes.'
    illustration: {fileID: 0}
    category: Combat
  - title: Combat & Damage
    bodyText: 'There is no separate attack button. Engaging an enemy in close-quarters
      combat (by moving directly adjacent to them) triggers a Dice Roll to determine
      your damage. You begin your journey with 2 dice, but as you progress, increasing
      your dice count is the key to unlocking devastating power. '
    illustration: {fileID: 0}
    category: Combat
  - title: The Dice Panel
    bodyText: 'Keep a close watch on the Dice Panel: high-impact combos and Critical
      Hits  (which multiply your total damage) are highlighted in real-time. Strategize
      with unique Perks to manipulate your rolls and bend the odds in your favor!'
    illustration: {fileID: 0}
    category: Combat
  - title: Enemy Bestiary
    bodyText: "1. Orc (The Brawler)\n\n\tBehavior: Moves directly toward the player
      and attacks once in \t\t\t   melee range.\n\n\tAttributes: High strength but
      low intelligence. Predictable    movement.\n\n\tStrategy: Easy to kite, but
      don't let them corner you!\n\n2. Hammer (The Crusher)\n\n\tBehavior: Channels
      a powerful area-of-effect (AoE) attack.\n\n\tMechanic: Displays a Red Hex warning
      tile before striking.\n\n\tSpawn Rate: Begins appearing after Level 2.\n\n\tStrategy:
      Step out of the highlighted zone immediately to avoid massive damage.\n\n3.
      Warlock (The Elusive Sniper)\n\n\tBehavior: A ranged specialist that maintains
      maximum distance.\n\n\tSpecial Move: Charges a deadly two-attack combo every
      3rd turn.\n\n\tDefense: Automatically teleports to a new location whenever
      it takes damage.\n\n\tSpawn Rate: Appears only after the first Boss level."
    illustration: {fileID: 0}
    category: Enemies
  - title: Boss & Special Mechanics
    bodyText: "4. Totem (The Protector) \n\n\tRole: Stationary structure that grants
      the Boss invulnerability.  \n\n\tChain Reaction: You must destroy all Totems
      to damage the Boss.  \n\n\tWave Mechanic: Breaking a Totem instantly clears
      all remaining minor enemies and triggers a new enemy wave.  \n\n5. The Boss
      (The Overlord) \n\n\tUltimate Attack: Readies an arena-wide blast every 3rd
      turn that hits every tile.  \n\n\tReactionary Defense: Teleports away from
      the player every time he is hit.  \n\n\tReinforcements: Spawns new minions
      each time he takes \tdamage. \n\n\tStrategy: Timing is everything\u2014break
      the Totems to drop his shield, then strike quickly before the arena-wide attack
      triggers!"
    illustration: {fileID: 0}
    category: Enemies
  - title: The Shop & Items
    bodyText: "The Shop is always accessible throughout your journey via the button
      located in the top-left corner of the screen. You don\u2019t need to wait for
      a room to clear; as long as you have the Gold, the Merchant\u2019s inventory
      is just a click away."
    illustration: {fileID: 0}
    category: Items
  - title: Currency and Rerolls
    bodyText: "Items provide a variety of persistent perks or immediate boosts to
      your combat efficiency. If the current selection doesn\u2019t suit your build,
      you can pay to Reroll the inventory. Be tactical with your spending, as the
      cost of rerolling increases each time you use it.\n"
    illustration: {fileID: 0}
    category: Items
  - title: Funding Your Run
    bodyText: "Gold is acquired by eliminating enemies. Efficient combat and specific
      Gold-boosting Perks are the best ways to ensure you can always afford the most
      powerful items in the Merchant\u2019s collection."
    illustration: {fileID: 0}
    category: Items
  - title: Enhancement Selection
    bodyText: After successfully clearing a room, you will be granted the opportunity
      to select a new Implant. These are permanent passive upgrades that integrate
      into your system and persist for the remainder of your run.
    illustration: {fileID: 0}
    category: Perks
  - title: Rarity & Scaling
    bodyText: 'Implants are categorized into five distinct tiers of rarity:


      Common
      (Grey)


      Rare (Blue)


      Epic (Purple)


      Legendary (Gold)


      ???
      (???)

'
    illustration: {fileID: 0}
    category: Perks
  - title: Synergies & Combinations
    bodyText: The key to a successful run lies in your ability to build Synergies.
      Experiment with different Implant combinations to unlock devastating technical
      advantages and create a build that can withstand any threat. Keep playing and
      you may find something interesting like -???-.
    illustration: {fileID: 0}
    category: Perks
  - title: Synergies & Combinations
    bodyText: At any point during your movement phase, you may choose to Skip your
      turn instead of relocating. This is a vital defensive maneuver. If you are
      already positioned adjacent to enemies when you Skip, you will immediately
      initiate a strike against them. Certain Implants are specifically engineered
      to provide massive bonuses when you choose to stand your ground and use this
      feature.
    illustration: {fileID: 0}
    category: Perks
